in": "Ethiopia, East Africa. Commercially important subspecies cultivated in India.", "traits": "Deep green leaves (often spotted when young), 1.5-2ft long, 3-4in broad. Densely rosulate, ensiform leaves. Marginal teeth large, deltoid, tipped with brown.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Limited availability in tropical monsoon climates. May be found through specialized medicinal plant nurseries or research institutions."}, {"name": "Aloe arborescens (Krantz Aloe)", "slug": "aloe-arborescens-krantz-aloe", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 9, "origin": "South Africa. Cultivated globally for medicinal and ornamental purposes.", "traits": "Large branching shrub, 1.8-2.4m tall. Multi-headed with narrow tooth-edged leaves in rosettes.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Available in India from medicinal plant nurseries and botanical gardens. Growing popularity for medicinal gardens."}], "variety_count": 18}'::jsonb,
