5m wide. Dense habit. Excellent for small gardens.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Banksia ''Bulli Baby''", "slug": "banksia-bulli-baby", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 19, "origin": "NSW coastal selection", "traits": "Compact dwarf 1.5m high x 1.2m wide. Extremely floriferous - 50-60 flower heads per season on mature plants.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Banksia ''Bronzed Aussie''", "slug": "banksia-bronzed-aussie", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 20, "origin": "Unknown origin. Propagated by Rod Parsons, Carawah Nursery. Seed given to Rod''s father by SGAP member many years ago, propagated vegetatively since.", "traits": "Medium shrub to 2m high. Unique bud clustering at base of main flower.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Available from Carawah Nursery and select retailers."}, {"name": "Banksia ''Roller Coaster''", "slug": "banksia-roller-coaster", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 21, "origin": "Coastal NSW selection. Also marketed as ''Austraflora Roller Coaster''.", "traits": "Vigorous prostrate groundcover spreading 4-5m wide but remaining only 50cm high. Excellent coastal tolerance.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Registered cultivar, available from Australian native plant nurseries."}, {"name": "Banksia ''Pygmy Possum''", "slug": "banksia-pygmy-possum", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 22, "origin": "Dwarf coastal form of Saw Banksia", "traits": "Prostrate groundcover with spreading growth. Low-growing form of normally 5-6m upright species.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Available from native plant specialists."}, {"name": "Banksia ''Mini Marg''", "slug": "banksia-mini-marg", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 23, "origin": "Selected compact form of Silver Banksia", "traits": "Compact shrub form, much smaller than typical 2-12m species range", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Available from southern Australian nurseries."}, {"name": "Banksia ''Yellow Wing''", "slug": "banksia-yellow-wing", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 24, "origin": "Deliberately hybridized by Austraflora", "traits": "Similar size to ''Coastal Cushion''. Named for frequent visits by New Holland honeyeaters.", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Available from Austraflora and select retailers."}, {"name": "Banksia coccinea (Scarlet Banksia) ⚠️ NOT SUITABLE", "slug": "banksia-coccinea-scarlet-banksia-not-suitable", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 25, "origin": "SW Western Australia (Denmark to Stirling Range)", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Banksia baxteri (Bird''s Nest Banksia) ⚠️ NOT SUITABLE", "slug": "banksia-baxteri-bird-s-nest-banksia-not-suitable", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 26, "origin": "SW Western Australia (Albany to Stirling Range)", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Banksia prionotes (Acorn Banksia) ⚠️ NOT SUITABLE", "slug": "banksia-prionotes-acorn-banksia-not-suitable", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 27, "origin": "SW Western Australia", "traits": "", "flesh_fruit": "", "yield_notes": "", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}], "variety_count": 28}'::jsonb,
