", "yield_notes": "Moderate yields", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR humid subtropical climates - Revered heirloom grown by artisanal orchardists. Unique chocolate appearance (not flavor). Connoisseur''s choice. Heat tolerant.", "availability": "Specialty nurseries, farmers markets (rare)"}, {"name": "Saijo", "slug": "saijo", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 17, "origin": "Japan, name means ''the very best one''", "traits": "Small to medium oblong, conical fruit; 1.5-2in long; bright orange; beautiful tree", "flesh_fruit": "Extremely sweet - honey-like; hints of mango/papaya; seedless; translucent when ripe", "yield_notes": "Productive; begins bearing 2-3 years", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Tanenashi", "slug": "tanenashi", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 18, "origin": "Japan, name translates to ''seedless''", "traits": "Medium-large conical fruit; light orange to red-orange skin; vigorous, upright tree to 30ft", "flesh_fruit": "Yellow-orange flesh; dry texture when ripe; sweet, rich flavor; completely seedless", "yield_notes": "Heavy, prolific producer; stores extremely well on tree", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Tamopan", "slug": "tamopan", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 19, "origin": "China, traditional variety", "traits": "Very large, flat fruit with distinctive ring constriction around middle; tomato with a hat shape; large tree to 30ft", "flesh_fruit": "Sweet when fully soft; orange flesh; unique appearance", "yield_notes": "Moderately productive", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Eureka", "slug": "eureka", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 20, "origin": "Selection developed in USA", "traits": "Medium-sized, flat-shaped fruit; red skin; small, relatively compact tree", "flesh_fruit": "Extremely high quality;