fully in humid subtropical climates.", "availability": "Daley''s Fruit, specialty nurseries"}, {"name": "Pomelo", "slug": "pomelo", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 24, "origin": "Selection", "traits": "Prolific bearer; large to extra-large fruit; deep orange", "flesh_fruit": "Very sweet when fully ripe; luscious jelly-like consistency", "yield_notes": "Prolific - very heavy bearer", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR humid subtropical climates - Heat tolerant. Extremely productive for home gardens.", "availability": "Daley''s Fruit"}, {"name": "Triumph (Tropical Persimmon, Sharon Fruit) 🌱", "slug": "triumph-tropical-persimmon-sharon-fruit", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 0, "origin": "Developed for warm climates; grown in Florida, Israel; name varies by region", "traits": "Small 6-7cm diameter; oblate shape; tomato-like appearance; thin, smooth skin; highly productive", "flesh_fruit": "Astringent when firm, but can be CO2-treated; dark orange-red when ripe; very soft, jelly-like when ready; seedless", "yield_notes": "Heavy, reliable crops in tropical conditions", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Fuyu", "slug": "fuyu", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 1, "origin": "Japan, late 1800s; name means ''winter''", "traits": "Round, squat fruit 5-7cm; bright orange; semi-dwarf to 15ft; heat-tolerant", "flesh_fruit": "Non-astringent; crisp and sweet when firm; seedless; excellent fresh eating", "yield_notes": "Heavy, consistent producer; self-pollinating", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Native to subtropical climates, tolerates heat and humidity very well. Requires minimal chill (100-200 hours). Can adapt to tropical conditions with proper care. Most widely grown persimmon globally. Heat zones 7-11 indicates good heat tolerance. Handles monsoon humidity. Self-fertile.", "availability": "M-Tech Gardens India, ZXXYANBI India (grafted plants), tropical monsoon climates nurseries, Amazon India"}, {"name": "Hachiya", "slug": "hachiya", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 2, "origin": "Japan, widely cultivated traditional variety", "traits": "Large acorn-shaped fruit; bright orange; vigorous tree", "flesh_fruit": "Astringent until soft; intensely sweet, honeyed; jelly-like; seedless", "yield_notes": "Productive; heavy bearer", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Requires hot summers to ripen fruit fully - tropical monsoon climates provides this. Best flavor and quality in warm climates. Heat zones 7-10. Self-fertile. Handles high heat well. May struggle with excessive monsoon moisture without proper drainage.", "availability": "Indian nurseries, Rudra Agro Nursery Pune, specialty tropical fruit suppliers"}, {"name": "Tanenashi", "slug": "tanenashi", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 3, "origin": "Japan, means ''seedless''", "traits": "Medium-large conical fruit; orange-red; vigorous tree", "flesh_fruit": "Yellow-orange; sweet, rich; completely seedless; dry texture", "yield_notes": "Heavy, prolific producer", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Eureka", "slug": "eureka", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 4, "origin": "USA selection", "traits": "Medium, flat fruit; red skin; compact tree; self-fruitful", "flesh_fruit": "Extremely high quality; contains seeds; stores well", "yield_notes": "Heavy producing; proven commercial variety", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Popular across Asia. Heat zones 8-11 indicating excellent heat tolerance. Can adapt to tropical conditions. Self-fertile advantage.", "availability": "International nurseries, specialty Indian suppliers"}, {"name": "Jiro (Ichikikei Jiro)", "slug": "jiro-ichikikei-jiro", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 5, "origin": "Japan, traditional cultivar from 1800s", "traits": "Large, square fruit; flat with lobes; compact tree 12-15ft", "flesh_fruit": "Non-astringent; firm, crisp, sweet; seedless; thin tender skin", "yield_notes": "Excellent when mature; productive", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Humidity tolerant. More cold-hardy than Fuyu but also heat-adaptable. Self-pollinating. Can handle tropical conditions with good drainage.", "availability": "Specialty nurseries in India, international suppliers"}, {"name": "Izu", "slug": "izu", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 6, "origin": "Japan, early variety", "traits": "Small to medium, tomato-shaped; bright orange; semi-dwarf", "flesh_fruit": "Non-astringent; sweet, crisp; pale orange flesh; seedless", "yield_notes": "Good cropping for tree size", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Early ripening suits tropical climate. Heat tolerant. More cold-hardy than Fuyu, indicating climate adaptability. Compact size good for tropical monsoon climates home gardens.", "availability": "Specialty Indian nurseries"}, {"name": "Suruga", "slug": "suruga", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 7, "origin": "Japan", "traits": "Medium-large fruit; reddish-orange skin", "flesh_fruit": "Very sweet - one of sweetest non-astringents; spicy-sweet; no astringency", "yield_notes": "Good production", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Researched for subtropical Australia (Queensland) indicating good heat/humidity tolerance. Heat zones 7-11. Can adapt to tropical conditions.", "availability": "Specialty nurseries"}, {"name": "Ormond", "slug": "ormond", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 8, "origin": "Florida selection, traditional variety", "traits": "2.5in long, 2in diameter; reddish-yellow outside, deep orange-red inside; fruits hang in clusters like grapes; vigorous tree", "flesh_fruit": "Very sweet, moderately juicy; astringent until soft; large seeds", "yield_notes": "Good production; cluster fruiting", "growing_notes": "EXCELLENT FOR tropical monsoon climates - SPECIFICALLY SUITED TO WARMER CLIMATES. Developed in Florida (similar tropical climate to tropical monsoon climates). Breaks bud early in spring, increasing chances of fruit set in tropical areas. Mid-sized tree suited to tropical monsoon climates conditions. Heat and humidity adapted.", "availability": "Florida nurseries, tropical fruit specialists"}, {"name": "Coffee Cake", "slug": "coffee-cake", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 9, "origin": "USA selection", "traits": "Brownish flesh; firm when ripe; medium-sized fruit", "flesh_fruit": "Sweet, rich, spicy - named after flavor; non-astringent; unique taste", "yield_notes": "Good yields; needs pollinator (Chocolate variety best)", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Heat zones 7-10. Ripens a month before Fuyu (fall/winter ripening). Warm climate adapted. Unique spiced flavor profile.", "availability": "Specialty nurseries, Four Winds Growers (USA)"}, {"name": "Chocolate (American Persimmon hybrid)", "slug": "chocolate-american-persimmon-hybrid", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 10, "origin": "USA, American persimmon variety", "traits": "Small to medium oblong fruit; bright red skin; chocolate-colored flesh", "flesh_fruit": "Firm, dotted chocolate specks; sweet with cocoa hints; non-astringent (rare for American type)", "yield_notes": "Good production; self-fruitful (rare for American persimmons)", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Heat zones 7-10. Heat tolerant. Self-fertile advantage. Unique chocolate flesh. Ripens late Oct-November.", "availability": "Four Winds Growers, specialty nurseries"}, {"name": "Diospyros kaki (Common Persimmon - Seedling Type) 🌱", "slug": "diospyros-kaki-common-persimmon-seedling-type", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 11, "origin": "Various regions - seedling selections; traditional types", "traits": "Variable traits; grown from seed; ornamental tree with orange autumn foliage", "flesh_fruit": "Quality varies; generally astringent; fruits in 5-7 years from seed", "yield_notes": "Variable depending on genetics", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Seedling persimmons often more adaptable to varied climates. Used as rootstock. Can produce in tropical/subtropical conditions. Available in tropical monsoon climates nurseries. More genetic diversity for climate adaptation. Good for tropical monsoon climates experimentation.", "availability": "tropical monsoon climates Garden, Zoropic Enterprise, M-Tech Gardens, local tropical monsoon climates nurseries"}, {"name": "Japani Phal (Local Indian Name)", "slug": "japani-phal-local-indian-name", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 12, "origin": "Traditional name in India for persimmon; multiple varieties sold under this name", "traits": "Variable - general term for persimmons in North India (Himachal, J&K, Uttarakhand)", "flesh_fruit": "Deep orange-red color; tomato-like appearance; soft, sweet when fully ripe", "yield_notes": "Variable", "growing_notes": "INDIGENOUS NAME IN INDIA - Cultivated in Indian temperate regions (Himachal, J&K, Tamil Nadu, Uttarakhand) but some selections may adapt to tropical monsoon climates with proper care. Look for heat-tolerant selections. Traditional Indian cultivation knowledge. Also known as Amarphal (Hindi).", "availability": "Indian nurseries nationwide, Rudra Agro Nursery Pune, regional nurseries"}, {"name": "Nikita''s Gift", "slug": "nikita-s-gift", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 13, "origin": "Ukraine/Russia, hybrid: Rosseyanka (D. kaki x D. virginiana) x D. kaki", "traits": "2.5-3in fruit; flat bottom; dark reddish-orange; small to medium tree", "flesh_fruit": "Exceptionally sweet when ripe; astringent; loses astringency easier than many varieties", "yield_notes": "Good production", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Very cold-hardy but ALSO heat-adaptable due to hybrid vigor. Ripens earlier than Saijo. Better for areas with long growing season but lacking extreme heat. Good for Tropical monsoon moderate heat with humidity.", "availability": "Stark Bros, specialty nurseries"}, {"name": "Rosseyanka", "slug": "rosseyanka", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 14, "origin": "Ukraine, hybrid: D. kaki x D. virginiana", "traits": "Small to medium fruit; American persimmon flavor profile", "flesh_fruit": "Very sweet; resembles American persimmon; astringent until soft", "yield_notes": "Very productive", "growing_notes": "SUITABLE FOR tropical monsoon climates - Very cold-hardy to -25°F but hybrid vigor gives climate adaptability. Can handle temperature extremes. Good for experimental tropical monsoon climates cultivation.", "availability": "Specialty nurseries, Trees of Joy"}], "variety_count": 40}'::jsonb,
