roductivity, one of largest blood plums", "growing_notes": "Low chill blood plum (300-400 hours), self-pollinating. Superb for cooler climates but will crop in subtropics. Cross-pollinate with Satsuma for best results. Unique to Daleys Nursery. Suitable for humid subtropical conditions. Ripens late January-early February.", "availability": "Daleys Nursery (exclusive)"}, {"name": "Amber Jewel", "slug": "amber-jewel", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 7, "origin": "Australian variety, developed in Australia", "traits": "Large fruit (63-70mm), red skin with yellow background, excellent shelf life", "flesh_fruit": "Amber flesh, super sweet, meaty crisp texture, unique flavor", "yield_notes": "Medium vigorous tree, large fruit production, high quality", "growing_notes": "Matures one month after Santa Rosa. Great storage capability. Partially self-fertile, Santa Rosa is compatible pollinator. Will make people come back for more due to exceptional sweetness. Ripens early February. Suitable for humid subtropical climates subtropical climate.", "availability": "Daleys Nursery, Australian nurseries"}, {"name": "Sunrise Gulf", "slug": "sunrise-gulf", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 8, "origin": "Florida breeding program", "traits": "Large purple fruits, medium to large red clingstone", "flesh_fruit": "Pale green/yellow flesh, sweet and juicy", "yield_notes": "Great quality fruits in warmer areas", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "A-Okay™", "slug": "a-okay", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 9, "origin": "Modern breeding program", "traits": "Modern low chill variety", "flesh_fruit": "Good quality, suitable for fresh eating", "yield_notes": "Reliable cropper in warm climates", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Yarrahapinni Blood", "slug": "yarrahapinni-blood", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_s