, "flesh_fruit": "Bright flavor, very sweet, excellent taste", "yield_notes": "Productive, prolific cropper", "growing_notes": "One of new generation of traditionally bred plums. Fruits early to mid-summer. Red to deep plum colored skin with mulberry red flesh. Suitable for cool temperate to warm areas. Suggested pollinator Mariposa. May adapt to humid subtropical climates with proper care.", "availability": "Daleys, Flower Power, specialty nurseries"}, {"name": "Donsworth", "slug": "donsworth", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 14, "origin": "Japanese blood plum, heritage variety", "traits": "Dark maroon with red/green spots, large freestone, egg-shaped fruit", "flesh_fruit": "Dark red flesh, tart skin but sweet flesh, excellent flavor", "yield_notes": "Good producer, large fruit if thinned", "growing_notes": "Old-fashioned blood plum. Stores and handles well - Taiwan market favorite after 16 days sea freight. Harvested mid-January. Pollinates with Narrabeen and Mariposa. Wide climate range adaptability including humid subtropical climates.", "availability": "PlantNet Australia, Australian commercial growers"}, {"name": "Queen Rosa", "slug": "queen-rosa", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 15, "origin": "Australian commercial variety", "traits": "Nice red color, good size, old-fashioned plum smell", "flesh_fruit": "Yellow flesh, sweet with slight tart skin", "yield_notes": "Good productivity, reliable cropper", "growing_notes": "Harvested early January. Classic plum characteristics with nostalgic appeal. Pollinates with Satsuma. Suitable for humid subtropical climates subtropical climate.", "availability": "Australian commercial fruit suppliers, Yalca"}, {"name": "Rose Zee", "slug": "rose-zee", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 16, "origin": "Early season Australian variety", "traits": "Red color, smallish fruit compare