ons. Leaves rusty-brown initially turning yellow then deep dark green. Rare in wild, used in landscaping for bright green foliage and purple-black fruits. Suitable for Tropical monsoon humid climate.", "availability": "Greens of tropical monsoon climates, specialty tropical fruit nurseries"}, {"name": "Kala Amritsari", "slug": "kala-amritsari", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 4, "origin": "Amritsar, Punjab, India - famous traditional variety", "traits": "Distinctively large size, darker skin compared to other Indian varieties", "flesh_fruit": "Yellowish flesh, extremely sweet flavor, juicy pulp", "yield_notes": "Highly productive, profuse flowering, high fruit set", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Satluj Purple", "slug": "satluj-purple", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 5, "origin": "Punjab, India - named after Sutlej River", "traits": "Dark purple skin with distinctive purplish-blue color, recognizable from distance", "flesh_fruit": "Very juicy and sweet, excellent for fresh juices and smoothies", "yield_notes": "Good productivity when cross-pollinated", "growing_notes": "Needs Kala Amritsari for cross-pollination. Low chill requirement suitable for warmer Indian climates. Grown in Punjab where Sutlej is primary river. Famous for juice production. May require adaptation trials in tropical monsoon climates conditions.", "availability": "Punjab nurseries, northern India suppliers"}, {"name": "Alucha", "slug": "alucha", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 6, "origin": "Not native to India but pervasively grown in Himachal Pradesh", "traits": "Bright red, sometimes maroonish hues, medium size", "flesh_fruit": "Flavors between sweet and sour, contrasting taste", "yield_notes": "High cultivation, abundantly available", "growing_notes": "Name means ''juicy edible fruit'' in Hindi. Generally used for chutneys and pickles due to contrasting flavors. Most abundantly available plum in India. Grown in hilly regions. Not suitable for Tropical monsoon lowland tropical conditions.", "availability": "Himachal Pradesh nurseries, northern hill regions"}, {"name": "Golden Japan", "slug": "golden-japan", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 7, "origin": "Japan, cultivated in India - Himachal Pradesh and Uttarakhand", "traits": "Golden yellow color, medium-sized, sometimes small yellow dots on surface", "flesh_fruit": "Very sweet but not overly sweet, balanced flavor", "yield_notes": "Harvested in July (peak monsoon)", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Santa Rosa (India)", "slug": "santa-rosa-india", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 8, "origin": "California USA, 1906, cultivated in India - J&K, Himachal Pradesh", "traits": "Purple with red blush, vibrant appearance", "flesh_fruit": "Very tender and juicy flesh, sweet with undertone of tartness", "yield_notes": "Good productivity in suitable climates", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Greengage (India cultivation)", "slug": "greengage-india-cultivation", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 9, "origin": "Iran origin, cultivated in Tamil Nadu for Indian market", "traits": "Greenish round fruit, not common green color for plums", "flesh_fruit": "Flavors similar to ripe mango, dried apricot, citrusy notes, versatile", "yield_notes": "Good for confectionery purposes", "growing_notes": "Best for confectionery due to versatile flavors. Cultivation in Tamil Nadu. Transported from Tamil Nadu to rest of country. High chill requirement limits tropical monsoon climates suitability, but Tamil Nadu proximity suggests possible adaptation in tropical monsoon climates highlands.", "availability": "Tamil Nadu nurseries, possibly tropical monsoon climates highland regions"}, {"name": "Titron", "sl