ds, smallest size, crunchiest texture, high fiber", "flesh_fruit": "Earthy, slightly sweet; firmest texture of all quinoas", "yield_notes": "Lower than other colors (500-800 kg/ha estimated)", "growing_notes": "Longest maturity time (110-130 days). Most heat-tolerant of the three colors but still challenged by humid subtropical climates climate. Slower germination. Best autumn planting. Thick seed coat somewhat protects against humidity.", "availability": "Limited; occasionally from specialty Australian seed companies"}, {"name": "Rainbow/Tri-Color Quinoa", "slug": "rainbow-tri-color-quinoa", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 3, "origin": "Mixed Andean sources", "traits": "Blend of white, red, and black seeds; visually appealing mix", "flesh_fruit": "Varied flavors and textures in one dish", "yield_notes": "Variable depending on color proportions", "growing_notes": "Popular consumer product. humid subtropical climates challenges same as individual colors. Winter growing only. Provides genetic diversity which may help with adaptation.", "availability": "Australian health food suppliers, some seed companies"}, {"name": "BEW / Kruso White", "slug": "bew-kruso-white", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 4, "origin": "Selected in Kununurra, Western Australia; released 2019", "traits": "White seeds, compact seed heads, late maturing, Australian-adapted", "flesh_fruit": "Good quality white grain", "yield_notes": "Up to 2-3 t/ha in ideal irrigated tropical conditions (Kununurra)", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Titicaca", "slug": "titicaca", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 5, "origin": "Denmark/Europe-bred from Bolivian germplasm", "traits": "White seeds, early maturity (90-110 days), uniform, photoperiod-insensitive", "flesh_fruit": "High-quality white grain, fluffy when cooked", "yield_notes": "2-3 t/ha in temperate