rness. Cultural importance in traditional Andean cuisine. Not viable outside high-altitude cool climates.", "availability": "Extremely limited; Andean seed conservation programs"}, {"name": "Kancolla (Blanca de Juli)", "slug": "kancolla-blanca-de-juli", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 12, "origin": "Lake Titicaca region, Peru", "traits": "White seeds, traditional lakeside variety", "flesh_fruit": "Good quality grain", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "Traditional variety from favorable Titicaca microclimate. Requires cool temperatures, moderate moisture. High-altitude crop. Not adapted to tropical lowlands.", "availability": "Peruvian seed banks"}, {"name": "Salcedo INIA", "slug": "salcedo-inia", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 13, "origin": "Peru (INIA breeding program), released 1990", "traits": "White seeds, improved variety, low saponin, disease resistant", "flesh_fruit": "Excellent grain quality, mild flavor", "yield_notes": "High in Andean conditions (3-4 t/ha)", "growing_notes": "One of Peru''s most successful improved varieties. Bred for Altiplano (3800-3900m elevation). Tolerates frost and drought of high Andes. NOT heat-tolerant. Unsuitable for tropical lowlands.", "availability": "INIA Peru; international research institutions"}, {"name": "Negra Collana (INIA 420)", "slug": "negra-collana-inia-420", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 14, "origin": "Puno, Peru (high Andes)", "traits": "Black seeds, traditional variety, high antioxidants", "flesh_fruit": "Earthy, distinctive flavor", "yield_notes": "Moderate", "growing_notes": "Traditional black quinoa variety. High nutritional value, rich in anthocyanins. High-altitude adapted. Long growing cycle (120+ days). Not suitable for tropical climates.", "availability": "Peruvian seed conservation"}, {"name": "Kaslala Multicolor", "slug": "kaslala-multicolor", "lineage_