ty for niche market sales.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Propagated by Sweets Strawberry Runners. Protected by Plant Breeders Rights (PBR)."}, {"name": "Rubygem", "slug": "rubygem", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 6, "origin": "Queensland, Australia", "traits": "Short-day variety producing from late autumn through early spring into summer. Low chill requirement.", "flesh_fruit": "High yields of moderately firm, attractive, juicy and delicious red fruit.", "yield_notes": "High yield producer suitable for Southeast Queensland strawberry-growing district.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Queensland nurseries and specialized strawberry plant suppliers."}, {"name": "Sundrench", "slug": "sundrench", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 7, "origin": "Queensland Department of Agriculture and Fisheries (QDAF), Australia", "traits": "Similar characteristics to Red Rhapsody with deep red exterior. High yielding variety for winter growing.", "flesh_fruit": "Deep red color throughout, good flavor and firmness.", "yield_notes": "Very high yielding for subtropical winter conditions.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Licensed nurseries throughout Queensland via commercial propagators."}, {"name": "Albion", "slug": "albion", "lineage_type": "hybrid", "climate_slug": "humid-subtropical", "sort_order": 8, "origin": "University of California, USA, 2006", "traits": "Day-neutral variety. Long, conical, symmetrical berries. Firm fruit bursting with sweetness. Most commonly planted variety in Victoria, Australia.", "flesh_fruit": "Very sweet with high sugar content. Large, firm berries with excellent shelf life. Consistent flavor profile.", "yield_notes": "High yields with good early season production. Produces continuously throughout growing season.", "growing_notes": "", "availability": "Widely available from Australian nurseries and online strawberry plant retailers."}, {"name": "