njab Safed 4 🌱", "slug": "punjab-safed-4", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 5, "origin": "Japan (Tokyo, Hakurei strains)", "traits": "Small white globe turnips, 5-8cm diameter", "flesh_fruit": "Sweet, crisp, mild; excellent raw", "yield_notes": "Fast maturing (30-40 days)", "growing_notes": "Recommended for Punjab/Haryana but worth trial in tropical monsoon climates during dry season. More heat-tolerant than temperate types. Asiatic breeding background suits warmer conditions. Trial planting in tropical monsoon climates December-January. May require irrigation management in Tropical monsoon high humidity.", "availability": "Punjab Agricultural University, North Indian seed suppliers, some availability through inter-state agricultural networks"}, {"name": "Golden Ball", "slug": "golden-ball", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 6, "origin": "Historical European variety, adapted globally", "traits": "Globe-shaped, golden-yellow, 8-12cm", "flesh_fruit": "Bright golden yellow, fine-grained, sweet mild flavor", "yield_notes": "65-70 days for full maturity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Snowball (Local adaptation)", "slug": "snowball-local-adaptation", "lineage_type": "heirloom", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 7, "origin": "Traditional variety with Indian cultivation history", "traits": "Round to globe-shaped, white, smooth", "flesh_fruit": "White, tender, mild sweet flavor", "yield_notes": "Medium maturity", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Local Red Round (Tropical type) 🌱", "slug": "local-red-round-tropical-type", "lineage_type": "indigenous", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 8, "origin": "India, tropical breeding background", "traits": "Red skin varieties adapted to warmer conditions", "flesh_fruit": "White flesh with variable rose coloring", "yield_notes": "Variable, adapted to local conditions", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}, {"name": "Turnip Greens Varieties", "slug": "turnip-greens-varieties", "lineage_type": "open_pollinated", "climate_slug": "tropical-monsoon", "sort_order": 9, "origin": "Various, selected for leaf production in warm climates", "traits": "Grown primarily for edible leaves; minimal root development", "flesh_fruit": "Tender, nutritious greens with mild peppery flavor", "yield_notes": "Multiple harvests, quick-growing leaves", "growing_notes": "", "availability": ""}], "variety_count": 21}'::jsonb,
